<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The assignment return_code = OS_ERROR at the start of OS_Console_CopyOut is redundant. The function enters a while(true) loop and every path that breaks out of the loop assigns return_code to either OS_SUCCESS (when the string terminator is found) or OS_QUEUE_FULL (when the buffer is full). There is no execution path that returns the initial OS_ERROR value, so removing the assignment would not change program behaviour — it is dead code and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
